{"TopicId":188484,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Mod keyboard","CreatedByName":"AstroPawian","CreatedById":175199,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-25T08:06:39Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"AstroPawian","CreatedById":175199,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-25T08:06:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy is this mod???\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022D4lt8OU.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002253.96\u0022 height=\u0022150\u0022 width=\u0022278\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/D4lt8OU.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-25T11:28:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/175199-astropawian/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022175199\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/175199-astropawian/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@AstroPawian\u003C/a\u003E, My guess would be so that when people are making instructional videos, the people watching said videos will know which keys are being pressed and when to associate them with the actions they\u0027re seeing in the video.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSimilar to a lot of Blender tutorials I\u0027ve seen, where they install an add-on that displays which keys are being pressed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, moving to Add-on Discussions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DStaal","CreatedById":155685,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-26T02:08:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs a long-time Dvorak user, I can see it being useful to me as well.\u00A0 Many of the keyboard controls (in this and a lot of other games) are laid out in a \u0027useful\u0027 but not necessarily mnemonic formation.\u00A0 Change the layout, and they can be hard to learn - just looking at that implies a few things to me about the control scheme for KSP that I\u0027ve never learnt because what keys do aren\u0027t linked to what the keys are other than by their placement.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-26T20:36:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223677060\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188484\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221569398799\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022175199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AstroPawian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/25/2019 at 4:06 AM, AstroPawian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy is this mod???\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022D4lt8OU.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002253.96\u0022 height=\u0022150\u0022 width=\u0022278\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/D4lt8OU.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery interesting, where did you see this?\u00A0 I\u0027ve done a lot of searching, but\u00A0can\u0027t find any mod which displays keys like that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lapis","CreatedById":193784,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-26T20:38:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmy guess would be an external program, or plugin for video editing software that overlays the keyboard onto the game after it is recorded.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-26T20:38:18Z\u0022 title=\u002212/26/2019 08:38  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 26, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Lapis\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-26T20:40:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223721299\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188484\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221577392683\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022193784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lapis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Lapis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmy guess would be an external program, or plugin for video editing software that overlays the keyboard onto the game after it is recorded.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMine too, was just wondering if there was a mod available.\u00A0 I never heard of one, so...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI found a nice list of virtual keyboards here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://thegeekpage.com/free-on-screen-virtual-keyboards/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://thegeekpage.com/free-on-screen-virtual-keyboards/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-26T20:42:13Z\u0022 title=\u002212/26/2019 08:42  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 26, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by linuxgurugamer\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}